I'd be willing to try and submit a PR. Do you have a guide for how to add new syscalls? Thank you for any pointers you can provide!

The following simple program triggers a stack overflow assuming a stack limit is set (default).

```c
void *global;

__attribute__((noinline)) void f(void)
{
    void *buff[1024];
    buff[0] = global;
    global = buff;
    asm volatile ("" :: "r"(buff) : "memory");
    f();
}

int main()
{
    f();
    return 0;
}
```

